metadata.name: Curiosity at the Gale Crater
metadata.description:
Curiosity is a rover designed to explore the Gale Crater on Mars as part of a NASA mission. Curiosity was launched on November 26, 2011 and landed on August 6, 2012 on the Aeolis Palus at the Gale Crater on Mars.
And this is an imaginary image of curiosity that I imagined in a dream.
